um luminosity to\npredict the BLR properties gives a much larger fraction of True Sy2 (about 90\\%\nof the unobscured Sy2 sample) than the use of the X-ray 2 keV luminosity (about\n20%). Nevertheless the number of AGN we securely detected as True Sy2 is at\nleast three times larger that the previously confirmed number of True Sy2.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 3 Aug 2016 10:05:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-10-19"}
