sts the presence of a\nnondisociative C-shock or a less energetic J-shock. The H2 1-0 S(1) continuum\nsubtracted image, reveals several knots and filaments at a larger spatial scale\naround IRS, in perfect matching with the distribution of the red and\nblueshifted molecular outflows discovered in our previous work.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 3 Aug 2016 12:47:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-10-05"}
